Overview

The Imaging Analyst role within the Imaging department of Property Insight is responsible for ensuring our client facing plants are kept current. This include working through tickets, discrepancies, analyzing data sets for gaps, and acquiring those gaps from their source.

Duties

• Review, analyze and make recommendations to convert various external image sources for ingestion into a standardized repository and format.• Manage the ingestion of current updates to the images from the external sources including updates to formats received and improvements to the ingestion processing. • Review and analysis of reports and insights to confirm currency or identify gaps that need remediated.• Analyzes problems and determines root causes.• Owns the remediation of problems end to end ensuring timely resolution for customers• Coordinates with internal and external stakeholders to receive and delivery imaging assets in a timely manner. • Ability to navigate competing priorities ensuring all deadlines are met.• Fully takes ownership of process and acts as an SME (subject matter expert).

Education

Bachelor’s degree in business administration, economics, computer science, management information systems or related field.

Experience

Minium of 1 year analyst experience or similar role that utilizes a similar skillset.

 

REQUIREMENTS:

 

• Strong attention to detail.• Desire to learn and drive efficiencies in existing processes.• Thrives in a team environment.• Problem solving, quantitative and analytical abilities.• Strong communication skills – both written and verbal.• Strong Excel skills.• Beginner SQL skills.

Additional Information

• One year Title industry experience• Experience with large datasets to identify and remediate issues

Overview

 

GIS Specialist

Westwood Professional Services, Inc.

 

Westwood Professional Services, Inc. is seeking a GIS Specialist to join our Renewables GIS team in our Minneapolis office. Westwood has a highly experienced and dynamic team of individuals dedicated to providing high-level professional services to our clients. 

Duties and Responsibilities

  • Work with clients and end users to build innovative GIS solutions using the ArcGIS platform
  • Perform complex GIS analysis using Esri's ArcGIS platform
  • Provide independent data interpretation while effectively maintaining data documentation.
  • Create and modify GIS datasets; manage and maintain legacy GIS datasets; develop and implement GIS-based analyses supporting renewable energy projects
  • Produce technically skilled and detailed solutions to include preparing clear, complete, and accurate representations of spatial data using ArcGIS Online and/or ArcGIS Enterprise
  • Process data and graphics requests from project team members and anticipate information needs and presentation format as part of renewable energy project workflows
  • Work with project stakeholders to develop and maintain new and useful workflows utilizing web-based GIS
  • Develop and maintain geospatial data on desktop, ArcGIS Online, ArcGIS Enterprise, and mobile applications. Ensure data meets appropriate data accuracy and content standards for quality assurance and quality control.

Required Experience

  • Must have a bachelor’s degree in GIS, geography, or related field with demonstrated capabilities in GIS.
  • Hands-on knowledge of ArcGIS Pro and ArcGIS Enterprise
  • Demonstrated ability to work with standard GIS datasets and deliverables
    • GDB, SHP, SDE (Enterprise), Vector, Raster, Feature Services, etc.
  • Experience using ArcGIS Online
    • Dashboards, Hub Sites, Webapp Builder, Story Maps, Field Maps, Survey123, etc.
  • Experience using Arcade, Python, ModelBuilder, or another common GIS scripting language
  • Experience working with different coordinate systems, map projections, and datums
  • Familiarity with standard cartographic methods, theories, and principles.
  • Ability to independently manage multiple assignments, determine and set job task priorities and work with limited direct supervision.

Preferred Experience

  • Previous work in/familiarity with consulting engineers and/or surveyors.
  • Experience using AutoCAD and DWG files
  • Experience using Google Earth and KMZ files.
  • Familiar with LiDAR datasets and usage
  • Experience as a consultant

Join us in creating a better world.

The team also serves as power users and thought leaders for Brex&#39;s own products. We bring precision and curiosity to everything we build, combining deep ownership with a product mindset to help shape the future of finance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As the Director of Tax, you will own and lead the end-to-end tax function. You will work cross-functionally across the organization within a detail-oriented environment, where creative problem-solving is highly valued. Additionally, you will serve as a key partner to the business as we continue to develop globally tax-compliant products for our customers. This role is critical for establishing scalable, efficient, and compliant tax operations across our growing landscape.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where you&#39;ll work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This role will be based in one of our Brex offices — San Francisco, New York, or Salt Lake City.&amp;nbsp;We are a hybrid environment that combines the energy and connections of being in the office with the benefits and flexibility of working from home. We currently require a minimum of two coordinated days in the office per week, Wednesday and Thursday. Starting February 2, 2026, we will require three days per week in office - Monday, Wednesday and Thursday. As a perk, we also have up to four weeks per year of fully remote work!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Lead all aspects of tax at Brex, including planning, strategy, financial reporting, and compliance&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Prepare or manage the preparation of all domestic and foreign tax and information returns&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Successfully navigate tax audits and examinations by all relevant authorities&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Ensure all tax accounts, including provisions, are properly reflected in relevant financial reporting&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Develop and improve tax systems, processes, and policies across the Company&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Manage the oversight of and partnership with external tax advisors as they provide coverage for our local and international operations&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Finance, People, Sales, Engineering, and other functions as needed&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Partner with Payroll and Equity functions in resolving employee-related tax issues&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Prepare journal entries and perform reconciliations over tax-related accounts&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Ensure all tax liabilities and obligations are met in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Ad-hoc projects, such as tax credits and incentive planning, as necessary&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;10+ years of public accounting or private industry experience covering domestic and international operations&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Ability to both manage a team and operate as an individual contributor to fulfill responsibilities&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Talented and highly motivated with a self-starter mentality&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal skills and ability to manage deadlines effectively&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical, problem-solving solving and decision-making skills&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Effective verbal, listening, and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CPA License&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Advanced Microsoft Office skills&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Credit card, payment processing, financial services and SaaS industry experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Knowledge and experience using NetSuite, Donnelly, Coupa, Looker and/or other data visualization software&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The expected salary range for this role is $235,040 - $279,110.&amp;nbsp; However, the starting base pay will depend on a number of factors including the candidate’s location, skills, experience, market demands, and internal pay parity. Depending on the position offered, equity and other forms of compensation may be provided as part of a total compensation package.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please be aware, job-seekers may be at risk of targeting by malicious actors looking for personal data.
